verses.text_plain: The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah concerning the dearth.
verses.verse_html:
1The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah concerning the dearth. ▼
▼ the dearth: Heb. the words of the dearths, or, restraints

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the dearth: Heb. the words of the dearths, or, restraints
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the dearth: Heb. the words of the dearths, or, restraints

verses.text_plain: Judah mourneth, and the gates thereof languish; they are black unto the ground; and the cry of Jerusalem is gone up.
verses.verse_html: 2Judah mourneth, and the gates thereof languish; they are black unto the ground; and the cry of Jerusalem is gone up.

verses.text_plain: And their nobles have sent their little ones to the waters: they came to the pits, and found no water; they returned with their vessels empty; they were ashamed and confounded, and covered their heads.
verses.verse_html: 3And their nobles have sent their little ones to the waters: they came to the pits, and found no water; they returned with their vessels empty; they were ashamed and confounded, and covered their heads.

verses.text_plain: Because the ground is chapt, for there was no rain in the earth, the plowmen were ashamed, they covered their heads.
verses.verse_html: 4Because the ground is chapt, for there was no rain in the earth, the plowmen were ashamed, they covered their heads.

verses.text_plain: Yea, the hind also calved in the field, and forsook it, because there was no grass.
verses.verse_html: 5Yea, the hind also calved in the field, and forsook it, because there was no grass.

verses.text_plain: And the wild asses did stand in the high places, they snuffed up the wind like dragons; their eyes did fail, because there was no grass.
verses.verse_html: 6And the wild asses did stand in the high places, they snuffed up the wind like dragons; their eyes did fail, because there was no grass.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, though our iniquities testify against us, do thou it for thy name’s sake: for our backslidings are many; we have sinned against thee.
verses.verse_html: 7O Lord, though our iniquities testify against us, do thou it for thy name’s sake: for our backslidings are many; we have sinned against thee.

verses.text_plain: O the hope of Israel, the saviour thereof in time of trouble, why shouldest thou be as a stranger in the land, and as a wayfaring man that turneth aside to tarry for a night?
verses.verse_html: 8O the hope of Israel, the saviour thereof in time of trouble, why shouldest thou be as a stranger in the land, and as a wayfaring man that turneth aside to tarry for a night?

tokens.text: why shouldest thou be as a stranger

verses.text_plain: Why shouldest thou be as a man astonied, as a mighty man that cannot save? yet thou, O Lord, art in the midst of us, and we are called by thy name; leave us not.
verses.verse_html:
9Why shouldest thou be as a man astonied, as a mighty man that cannot save? yet thou, O Lord, art in the midst of us, and we are called by thy name; leave us not. ▼
▼ we…: Heb. thy name is called upon us

tokens.text: Why shouldest thou be as a man
of us, and we are called

footnotes.body_text: ▼ we…: Heb. thy name is called upon us
footnotes.body_html: ▼ we…: Heb. thy name is called upon us

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord unto this people, Thus have they loved to wander, they have not refrained their feet, therefore the Lord doth not accept them; he will now remember their iniquity, and visit their sins.
verses.verse_html: 10Thus saith the Lord unto this people, Thus have they loved to wander, they have not refrained their feet, therefore the Lord doth not accept them; he will now remember their iniquity, and visit their sins.

verses.text_plain: Then said the Lord unto me, Pray not for this people for their good.
verses.verse_html: 11Then said the Lord unto me, Pray not for this people for their good.

verses.text_plain: When they fast, I will not hear their cry; and when they offer burnt offering and an oblation, I will not accept them: but I will consume them by the sword, and by the famine, and by the pestilence.
verses.verse_html: 12When they fast, I will not hear their cry; and when they offer burnt offering and an oblation, I will not accept them: but I will consume them by the sword, and by the famine, and by the pestilence.

verses.text_plain: Then said I, Ah, Lord God! behold, the prophets say unto them, Ye shall not see the sword, neither shall ye have famine; but I will give you assured peace in this place.
verses.verse_html:
13Then said I, Ah, Lord God! behold, the prophets say unto them, Ye shall not see the sword, neither shall ye have famine; but I will give you assured peace in this place. ▼
▼ assured…: Heb. peace of truth

tokens.text: unto them, Ye shall not see

footnotes.body_html: ▼ assured…: Heb. peace of truth

verses.text_plain: Then the Lord said unto me, The prophets prophesy lies in my name: I sent them not, neither have I commanded them, neither spake unto them: they prophesy unto you a false vision and divination, and a thing of nought, and the deceit of their heart.
verses.verse_html: 14Then the Lord said unto me, The prophets prophesy lies in my name: I sent them not, neither have I commanded them, neither spake unto them: they prophesy unto you a false vision and divination, and a thing of nought, and the deceit of their heart.

tokens.text: them not, neither have I commanded

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord concerning the prophets that prophesy in my name, and I sent them not, yet they say, Sword and famine shall not be in this land; By sword and famine shall those prophets be consumed.
verses.verse_html: 15Therefore thus saith the Lord concerning the prophets that prophesy in my name, and I sent them not, yet they say, Sword and famine shall not be in this land; By sword and famine shall those prophets be consumed.

tokens.text: shall not be in this land

verses.text_plain: And the people to whom they prophesy shall be cast out in the streets of Jerusalem because of the famine and the sword; and they shall have none to bury them, them, their wives, nor their sons, nor their daughters: for I will pour their wickedness upon them.
verses.verse_html: 16And the people to whom they prophesy shall be cast out in the streets of Jerusalem because of the famine and the sword; and they shall have none to bury them, them, their wives, nor their sons, nor their daughters: for I will pour their wickedness upon them.

tokens.text: and they shall have none to bury

verses.text_plain: Therefore thou shalt say this word unto them; Let mine eyes run down with tears night and day, and let them not cease: for the virgin daughter of my people is broken with a great breach, with a very grievous blow.
verses.verse_html: 17Therefore thou shalt say this word unto them; Let mine eyes run down with tears night and day, and let them not cease: for the virgin daughter of my people is broken with a great breach, with a very grievous blow.

verses.text_plain: If I go forth into the field, then behold the slain with the sword! and if I enter into the city, then behold them that are sick with famine! yea, both the prophet and the priest go about into a land that they know not.
verses.verse_html:
18If I go forth into the field, then behold the slain with the sword! and if I enter into the city, then behold them that are sick with famine! yea, both the prophet and the priest go about into a land that they know not. ▼
▼ go about…: or, make merchandise against a land, and men acknowledge it not

tokens.text: then behold them that are sick

footnotes.body_text: ▼ go about…: or, make merchandise against a land, and men acknowledge it not
footnotes.body_html: ▼ go about…: or, make merchandise against a land, and men acknowledge it not

verses.text_plain: Hast thou utterly rejected Judah? hath thy soul lothed Zion? why hast thou smitten us, and there is no healing for us? we looked for peace, and there is no good; and for the time of healing, and behold trouble!
verses.verse_html: 19Hast thou utterly rejected Judah? hath thy soul lothed Zion? why hast thou smitten us, and there is no healing for us? we looked for peace, and there is no good; and for the time of healing, and behold trouble!

verses.text_plain: We acknowledge, O Lord, our wickedness, and the iniquity of our fathers: for we have sinned against thee.
verses.verse_html: 20We acknowledge, O Lord, our wickedness, and the iniquity of our fathers: for we have sinned against thee.

verses.text_plain: Do not abhor us, for thy name’s sake, do not disgrace the throne of thy glory: remember, break not thy covenant with us.
verses.verse_html: 21Do not abhor us, for thy name’s sake, do not disgrace the throne of thy glory: remember, break not thy covenant with us.

verses.text_plain: Are there any among the vanities of the Gentiles that can cause rain? or can the heavens give showers? art not thou he, O Lord our God? therefore we will wait upon thee: for thou hast made all these things.
verses.verse_html: 22Are there any among the vanities of the Gentiles that can cause rain? or can the heavens give showers? art not thou he, O Lord our God? therefore we will wait upon thee: for thou hast made all these things.

tokens.text: upon thee: for thou hast made
